  <h1>
   camera_set_view_pos
  </h1>
  You can use this function to update the position of the camera view within the room. You give the unique camera ID value (as returned by the different
  <span>
   <a href="camera_create.htm">
    camera_create()
   </a>
  </span>
  functions) and then give the x and y positions
    to set the camera to.
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">camera_set_view_pos(camera_id, x, y)
</code></pre>
  <table>
   <tbody>
    <tr>
     <th>
      Argument
     </th>
     <th>
      Type
     </th>
     <th>
      Description
     </th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      camera_id
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Reference/Cameras_And_Display/Cameras_And_Viewports/camera_create.htm">
        Camera ID
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The unique camera ID value returned when you created the camera.
     </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      x
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
        Real
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The x position to place the view at (in the room)
     </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      y
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
        Real
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The y position to place the view at (in the room)
     </td>
    </tr>
   </tbody>
  </table>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">N/A
</code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">camera_set_view_pos(view_camera[0], x - (view_wport[0] / 2), y - (view_hport[0] / 2));
</code></pre>
  The above code will set the view camera position for the camera assigned to view port[0].
 </body>
